\|WMU is better then Markdown and simpler then Latex. 

|h2|Main goal

The main goal of WMU is to create a markup language that supports all of the elements found in books.

|h2|Concrete goals

|list
|=
|as simple as possible and easy to remember
|convention over configuration

|h2|=Main differences from Markdown

|list
|=
- better control over empty lines
- automatic (but opptional) table of contents
- support of notes
